    {
      "title": "李影",
      "url": "https://ss.pku.edu.cn/sztd/xssbsz/cd38cb490d9648ba863cffea67a1a941.htm",
      "url_hash": "a48d23a726c5f84abdc74576fd23b746137ba7dcfd210a43ba60e43e456100e3",
      "published_at": null,
      "author": null,
      "content": "Ying Li is currently a professor of the School of Software and Microelectronics in Peking University. Meanwhile, she is a research professor of National Research Center of Software Engineering, and managing the Education Center of Doctor of Engineering (electronics and information area). Before joining PKU in 2012, she worked as STSM and Senior Manager leading the Department of Distributed Computing and Service Management in IBM China Research Lab.During the period of working in IBM, Dr. Li conducted several global collaborative research projects that the technologies have been successfully delivered and transformed to IBM software products and global service solutions, which made significant technology impact and business value, wining \"IBM CIO Leadership Award\" (2007) and \"IBM Global Research Accomplishment Award\" twice (2008 and 2010). She worked as the Executive Assistant to IBM China Chairman in 2009. She worked as the member of Software Product Architecture Board to participate several industrial projects with solid contribution to commercial software systems. She also worked as the Strategist for IBM global research strategy, and contributed to IBM Global Technical Outlook (GTO) from year 2008 to 2011. She had served as the Chair of IBM Research Lab Patent Review Board for several years. She was awarded as the \"IBM Master Inventor\" in 2011.During the period of working in PKU, research interests including Artificial Intelligence for IT Operations, Cloud-Native systems, distributed machine learning and natural language processing, etc. She and her research team have undertaking relevant research projects supported by National Key Research and Development Program, National Natural Science Foundation, Key-Area R&D program of Guangdong Province, etc. and building fruitful collaboration with high tech companies including Delta，ZTE, Alibaba, Huawei, ICBC Tech, UINO, IBM, VMware etc. to solve challenging technical problems in industry.Professor Li applied 30+ US/CN patents wherein 33 US/CN patents were granted. She has published 90+ academic papers on top international journals and conferences. She served as reviewers for top international conferences including ACL, IJCAI, AAAI, etc., and the senior member of CCF.",
